    <div class="grid-12 body-text">
        <p class="cols-left-half">
            The top was created from four 7" boards. The edges were first made square by <a href="https://brfinewoodworking.com/edge-jointing-using-the-match-planing-method/">match planing</a>. Because of their size, this needed to be done using the bench surface as a giant <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shooting_board">shooting board</a>. The prepped boards were then glued into a single panel using pipe clamps and <a href="https://www.finewoodworking.com/2011/03/08/clamping-cauls-the-secret-to-great-glue-ups">cauls</a>. 
        </p>
